 :clean: 1. /adj./ Used of hardware or software designs, implies `elegance in
the small', that is, a design or implementation that may not hold any
surprises but does things in a way that is reasonably intuitive and
relatively easy to comprehend from the outside. The antonym is `grungy' or
{crufty}. 2. /v./ To remove unneeded or undesired files in a effort to reduce
clutter: "I'm cleaning up my account." "I cleaned up the garbage and now have
100 Meg free on that partition."